China is close to completing its first blood bank for pandas, aiding in genetic diversity and blood transfusions.
The Qinling pandas, a sub-species of the giant panda, are facing threats from blooming bamboo, leading to hunger among the population.
To protect the endangered species, China has established nature reserves and applied for UN protection.
Efforts to expand panda habitats in provinces like Shaanxi are underway, with initiatives to restore and protect natural forest resources.
Despite challenges like frost and food scarcity, conservation efforts continue to safeguard the iconic giant panda population.
